# Tutorial 1: Simple Melody
# ========================
#
# Welcome to MIDI Markup Language! This tutorial will teach you the basics
# by creating a simple melody. We'll cover:
#
# 1. Absolute timing [mm:ss.ms] - when notes happen
# 2. note_on and note_off commands - creating notes
# 3. Basic rhythm patterns - quarter notes, eighth notes, half notes
# 4. Musical phrasing - rests and articulation
#
# For more details, see: docs/tutorials/basic-melody.md

# TIMING BASICS
# =============
# Absolute timing uses the format [mm:ss.ms] where:
#   mm  = minutes (00-99)
#   ss  = seconds (00-59)
#   ms  = milliseconds (000-999)
#
# At tempo 100 BPM:
#   - One quarter note = 0.6 seconds = 600ms
#   - One eighth note = 0.3 seconds = 300ms
#   - One half note = 1.2 seconds = 1200ms
#   - One whole note = 2.4 seconds = 2400ms

# MIDI COMMANDS
# =============
# note_on channel.note velocity duration
#   channel  = MIDI channel (1-16)
#   note     = MIDI note number (0-127) or name (C4, D#5, etc.)
#   velocity = how hard the note is hit (0-127, where 127 is loudest)
#   duration = how long the note lasts (1b = 1 beat, 2b = 2 beats, etc.)
#
# We'll use channel 1 for our melody (piano sound in most MIDI players)

